{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1119,"text":"So in 1781, an English composer,"},{"time":4590,"text":"technologist and astronomer called William Herschel"},{"time":7729,"text":"noticed an object on the sky that"},{"time":9472,"text":"didn't quite move the way the rest of the stars did."},{"time":12340,"text":"And Herschel's recognition\nthat something was different,"},{"time":15434,"text":"that something wasn't quite right,"},{"time":17301,"text":"was the discovery of a planet,"},{"time":19123,"text":"the planet Uranus,"},{"time":21200,"text":"a name that has entertained"},{"time":22555,"text":"countless generations of children,"},{"time":25715,"text":"but a planet that overnight"},{"time":28050,"text":"doubled the size of our known solar system."},{"time":30666,"text":"Just last month, NASA announced the discovery"},{"time":32521,"text":"of 517 new planets"},{"time":34850,"text":"in orbit around nearby stars,"},{"time":36976,"text":"almost doubling overnight the number of planets"},{"time":39227,"text":"we know about within our galaxy."},{"time":41825,"text":"So astronomy is constantly being transformed by this"},{"time":44457,"text":"capacity to collect data,"},{"time":46595,"text":"and with data almost doubling every year,"},{"time":49140,"text":"within the next two decades, me may even"},{"time":50948,"text":"reach the point for the first time in history"},{"time":53266,"text":"where we've discovered the majority of the galaxies"},{"time":56120,"text":"within the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57844,"text":"But as we enter this era of big data,"},{"time":60128,"text":"what we're beginning to find is there's a difference"},{"time":62108,"text":"between more data being just better"},{"time":65269,"text":"and more data being different,"},{"time":67249,"text":"capable of changing the questions we want to ask,"},{"time":70140,"text":"and this difference is not about\nhow much data we collect,"},{"time":73460,"text":"it's whether those data open new windows"},{"time":75149,"text":"into our universe,"},{"time":76527,"text":"whether they change the way we view the sky."},{"time":79412,"text":"So what is the next window into our universe?"},{"time":82851,"text":"What is the next chapter for astronomy?"},{"time":85642,"text":"Well, I'm going to show you some\nof the tools and the technologies"},{"time":88297,"text":"that we're going to develop over the next decade,"},{"time":90861,"text":"and how these technologies,"},{"time":92334,"text":"together with the smart use of data,"},{"time":94202,"text":"may once again transform astronomy"},{"time":97172,"text":"by opening up a window into our universe,"},{"time":99219,"text":"the window of time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101000,"text":"Why time? Well, time is about origins,"},{"time":103584,"text":"and it's about evolution."},{"time":105474,"text":"The origins of our solar system,"},{"time":106970,"text":"how our solar system came into being,"},{"time":109174,"text":"is it unusual or special in any way?"},{"time":112583,"text":"About the evolution of our universe."},{"time":114574,"text":"Why our universe is continuing to expand,"},{"time":117580,"text":"and what is this mysterious dark energy"},{"time":119513,"text":"that drives that expansion?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":122128,"text":"But first, I want to show you how technology"},{"time":124892,"text":"is going to change the way we view the sky."},{"time":127663,"text":"So imagine if you were sitting"},{"time":129170,"text":"in the mountains of northern Chile"},{"time":131262,"text":"looking out to the west"},{"time":132669,"text":"towards the Pacific Ocean"},{"time":134717,"text":"a few hours before sunrise."},{"time":137281,"text":"This is the view of the night sky that you would see,"},{"time":140518,"text":"and it's a beautiful view,"},{"time":142189,"text":"with the Milky Way just peeking out over the horizon."},{"time":145102,"text":"but it's also a static view,"},{"time":147262,"text":"and in many ways, this is the\nway we think of our universe:"},{"time":150020,"text":"eternal and unchanging."},{"time":152414,"text":"But the universe is anything but static."},{"time":154405,"text":"It constantly changes on timescales of seconds"},{"time":156936,"text":"to billions of years."},{"time":158781,"text":"Galaxies merge, they collide"},{"time":160525,"text":"at hundreds of thousands of miles per hour."},{"time":163180,"text":"Stars are born, they die,"},{"time":165250,"text":"they explode in these extravagant displays."},{"time":168400,"text":"In fact, if we could go back"},{"time":169670,"text":"to our tranquil skies above Chile,"},{"time":172269,"text":"and we allow time to move forward"},{"time":174734,"text":"to see how the sky might change over the next year,"},{"time":179127,"text":"the pulsations that you see"},{"time":181417,"text":"are supernovae, the final remnants of a dying star"},{"time":185826,"text":"exploding, brightening and then fading from view,"},{"time":189573,"text":"each one of these supernovae"},{"time":191463,"text":"five billion times the brightness of our sun,"},{"time":194466,"text":"so we can see them to great distances"},{"time":196806,"text":"but only for a short amount of time."},{"time":199302,"text":"Ten supernova per second explode somewhere"},{"time":201879,"text":"in our universe."},{"time":203296,"text":"If we could hear it,"},{"time":204716,"text":"it would be popping like a bag of popcorn."},{"time":208415,"text":"Now, if we fade out the supernovae,"},{"time":211542,"text":"it's not just brightness that changes."},{"time":214771,"text":"Our sky is in constant motion."},{"time":217110,"text":"This swarm of objects you\nsee streaming across the sky"},{"time":220280,"text":"are asteroids as they orbit our sun,"},{"time":222938,"text":"and it's these changes and the motion"},{"time":224910,"text":"and it's the dynamics of the system"},{"time":227234,"text":"that allow us to build our models for our universe,"},{"time":229607,"text":"to predict its future and to explain its past."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233680,"text":"But the telescopes we've used over the last decade"},{"time":236774,"text":"are not designed to capture the data at this scale."},{"time":240789,"text":"The Hubble Space Telescope:"},{"time":242409,"text":"for the last 25 years it's been producing"},{"time":244670,"text":"some of the most detailed views"},{"time":246631,"text":"of our distant universe,"},{"time":248622,"text":"but if you tried to use the Hubble to create an image"},{"time":250692,"text":"of the sky, it would take 13 million individual images,"},{"time":255270,"text":"about 120 years to do this just once."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258982,"text":"So this is driving us to new technologies"},{"time":261243,"text":"and new telescopes,"},{"time":263090,"text":"telescopes that can go faint"},{"time":264832,"text":"to look at the distant universe"},{"time":266385,"text":"but also telescopes that can go wide"},{"time":269066,"text":"to capture the sky as rapidly as possible,"},{"time":271885,"text":"telescopes like the Large Synoptic Survey Telescope,"},{"time":275446,"text":"or the LSST,"},{"time":277325,"text":"possibly the most boring name ever"},{"time":279665,"text":"for one of the most fascinating experiments"},{"time":281644,"text":"in the history of astronomy,"},{"time":283636,"text":"in fact proof, if you should need it,"},{"time":285850,"text":"that you should never allow \na scientist or an engineer"},{"time":288518,"text":"to name anything, not even your children.\n(Laughter)"},{"time":294349,"text":"We're building the LSST."},{"time":295814,"text":"We expect it to start taking data\nby the end of this decade."},{"time":299195,"text":"I'm going to show you how we think"},{"time":300894,"text":"it's going to transform \nour views of the universe,"},{"time":304471,"text":"because one image from the LSST"},{"time":306845,"text":"is equivalent to 3,000 images"},{"time":309230,"text":"from the Hubble Space Telescope,"},{"time":311356,"text":"each image three and a half degrees on the sky,"},{"time":314494,"text":"seven times the width of the full moon."},{"time":317270,"text":"Well, how do you capture an image at this scale?"},{"time":319579,"text":"Well, you build the largest digital camera in history,"},{"time":323730,"text":"using the same technology you find\nin the cameras in your cell phone"},{"time":326891,"text":"or in the digital cameras you \ncan buy in the High Street,"},{"time":330682,"text":"but now at a scale that is five and a half feet across,"},{"time":333802,"text":"about the size of a Volkswagen Beetle,"},{"time":336210,"text":"where one image is three billion pixels."},{"time":339168,"text":"So if you wanted to look at an image"},{"time":340506,"text":"in its full resolution, just a single LSST image,"},{"time":343735,"text":"it would take about 1,500 \nhigh-definition TV screens."},{"time":348460,"text":"And this camera will image the sky,"},{"time":351238,"text":"taking a new picture every 20 seconds,"},{"time":354276,"text":"constantly scanning the sky"},{"time":356464,"text":"so every three nights, we'll get a completely new view"},{"time":359289,"text":"of the skies above Chile."},{"time":361672,"text":"Over the mission lifetime of this telescope,"},{"time":364507,"text":"it will detect 40 billion stars and galaxies,"},{"time":367859,"text":"and that will be for the first time"},{"time":369359,"text":"we'll have detected more objects in our universe"},{"time":372134,"text":"than people on the Earth."},{"time":374823,"text":"Now, we can talk about this"},{"time":376038,"text":"in terms of terabytes and petabytes"},{"time":378400,"text":"and billions of objects,"},{"time":379919,"text":"but a way to get a sense of the amount of data"},{"time":381667,"text":"that will come off this camera"},{"time":383566,"text":"is that it's like playing every TED Talk ever recorded"},{"time":388297,"text":"simultaneously, 24 hours a day,"},{"time":391370,"text":"seven days a week, for 10 years."},{"time":394228,"text":"And to process this data means"},{"time":396489,"text":"searching through all of those talks"},{"time":398413,"text":"for every new idea and every new concept,"},{"time":400662,"text":"looking at each part of the video"},{"time":402518,"text":"to see how one frame may have changed"},{"time":404543,"text":"from the next."},{"time":406388,"text":"And this is changing the way that we do science,"},{"time":408739,"text":"changing the way that we do astronomy,"},{"time":410994,"text":"to a place where software and algorithms"},{"time":413250,"text":"have to mine through this data,"},{"time":415118,"text":"where the software is as critical to the science"},{"time":418324,"text":"as the telescopes and the \ncameras that we've built."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422351,"text":"Now, thousands of discoveries"},{"time":424938,"text":"will come from this project,"},{"time":426873,"text":"but I'm just going to tell you about two"},{"time":428324,"text":"of the ideas about origins and evolution"},{"time":430687,"text":"that may be transformed by our access"},{"time":432940,"text":"to data at this scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435501,"text":"In the last five years, NASA has discovered"},{"time":437886,"text":"over 1,000 planetary systems"},{"time":440147,"text":"around nearby stars,"},{"time":442240,"text":"but the systems we're finding"},{"time":444170,"text":"aren't much like our own solar system,"},{"time":446660,"text":"and one of the questions we face is"},{"time":448235,"text":"is it just that we haven't been looking hard enough"},{"time":450553,"text":"or is there something special or unusual"},{"time":452319,"text":"about how our solar system formed?"},{"time":454737,"text":"And if we want to answer that question,"},{"time":456999,"text":"we have to know and understand"},{"time":458438,"text":"the history of our solar system in detail,"},{"time":461274,"text":"and it's the details that are crucial."},{"time":463411,"text":"So now, if we look back at the sky,"},{"time":467077,"text":"at our asteroids that were streaming across the sky,"},{"time":470628,"text":"these asteroids are like the\ndebris of our solar system."},{"time":474850,"text":"The positions of the asteroids"},{"time":476858,"text":"are like a fingerprint of an earlier time"},{"time":478995,"text":"when the orbits of Neptune and Jupiter"},{"time":480975,"text":"were much closer to the sun,"},{"time":482870,"text":"and as these giant planets migrated\nthrough our solar system,"},{"time":486323,"text":"they were scattering the asteroids in their wake."},{"time":489653,"text":"So studying the asteroids"},{"time":490959,"text":"is like performing forensics,"},{"time":493080,"text":"performing forensics on our solar system,"},{"time":495638,"text":"but to do this, we need distance,"},{"time":498340,"text":"and we get the distance from the motion,"},{"time":500419,"text":"and we get the motion because of our access to time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504966,"text":"So what does this tell us?"},{"time":506668,"text":"Well, if you look at the little yellow asteroids"},{"time":508895,"text":"flitting across the screen,"},{"time":511168,"text":"these are the asteroids that are moving fastest,"},{"time":513598,"text":"because they're closest to us, closest to Earth."},{"time":516939,"text":"These are the asteroids we may one day"},{"time":518446,"text":"send spacecraft to, to mine them for minerals,"},{"time":521844,"text":"but they're also the asteroids that may one day"},{"time":523846,"text":"impact the Earth,"},{"time":525511,"text":"like happened 60 million years ago"},{"time":526802,"text":"with the extinction of the dinosaurs,"},{"time":529437,"text":"or just at the beginning of the last century,"},{"time":531259,"text":"when an asteroid wiped out"},{"time":532591,"text":"almost 1,000 square miles of Siberian forest,"},{"time":536180,"text":"or even just last year, as one burnt up over Russia,"},{"time":539268,"text":"releasing the energy of a small nuclear bomb."},{"time":542880,"text":"So studying the forensics of our solar system"},{"time":546502,"text":"doesn't just tell us about the past,"},{"time":548560,"text":"it can also predict the future, \nincluding our future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554771,"text":"Now when we get distance,"},{"time":556739,"text":"we get to see the asteroids \nin their natural habitat,"},{"time":560328,"text":"in orbit around the sun."},{"time":561650,"text":"So every point in this visualization that you can see"},{"time":564557,"text":"is a real asteroid."},{"time":567320,"text":"Its orbit has been calculated\nfrom its motion across the sky."},{"time":571330,"text":"The colors reflect the composition of these asteroids,"},{"time":574671,"text":"dry and stony in the center,"},{"time":576808,"text":"water-rich and primitive towards the edge,"},{"time":579395,"text":"water-rich asteroids which may have seeded"},{"time":581679,"text":"the oceans and the seas that we find on our planet"},{"time":585130,"text":"when they bombarded the \nEarth at an earlier time."},{"time":590127,"text":"Because the LSST will be able to go faint"},{"time":592959,"text":"and not just wide,"},{"time":594657,"text":"we will be able to see these asteroids"},{"time":596465,"text":"far beyond the inner part of our solar system,"},{"time":599652,"text":"to asteroids beyond the \norbits of Neptune and Mars,"},{"time":603465,"text":"to comets and asteroids that may exist"},{"time":605726,"text":"almost a light year from our sun."},{"time":608956,"text":"And as we increase the detail of this picture,"},{"time":611565,"text":"increasing the detail by factors of 10 to 100,"},{"time":614692,"text":"we will be able to answer questions such as,"},{"time":617122,"text":"is there evidence for planets\noutside the orbit of Neptune,"},{"time":620711,"text":"to find Earth-impacting asteroids"},{"time":623218,"text":"long before they're a danger,"},{"time":625753,"text":"and to find out whether, maybe,"},{"time":627510,"text":"our sun formed on its own or in a cluster of stars,"},{"time":630690,"text":"and maybe it's this sun's stellar siblings"},{"time":633772,"text":"that influenced the formation of our solar system,"},{"time":637214,"text":"and maybe that's one of the reasons why \nsolar systems like ours seem to be so rare."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642974,"text":"Now, distance and changes in our universe —"},{"time":647536,"text":"distance equates to time,"},{"time":651395,"text":"as well as changes on the sky."},{"time":653454,"text":"Every foot of distance you look away,"},{"time":656244,"text":"or every foot of distance an object is away,"},{"time":658729,"text":"you're looking back about a\nbillionth of a second in time,"},{"time":662318,"text":"and this idea or this notion of looking back in time"},{"time":664931,"text":"has revolutionized our ideas about the universe,"},{"time":667562,"text":"not once but multiple times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669842,"text":"The first time was in 1929,"},{"time":672654,"text":"when an astronomer called Edwin Hubble"},{"time":674746,"text":"showed that the universe was expanding,"},{"time":676995,"text":"leading to the ideas of the Big Bang."},{"time":679708,"text":"And the observations were simple:"},{"time":682290,"text":"just 24 galaxies"},{"time":684444,"text":"and a hand-drawn picture."},{"time":689124,"text":"But just the idea that the more distant a galaxy,"},{"time":693784,"text":"the faster it was receding,"},{"time":695854,"text":"was enough to give rise to modern cosmology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699273,"text":"A second revolution happened 70 years later,"},{"time":701698,"text":"when two groups of astronomers showed"},{"time":703770,"text":"that the universe wasn't just expanding,"},{"time":706203,"text":"it was accelerating,"},{"time":707528,"text":"a surprise like throwing up a ball into the sky"},{"time":710871,"text":"and finding out the higher that it gets,"},{"time":713683,"text":"the faster it moves away."},{"time":715461,"text":"And they showed this"},{"time":716970,"text":"by measuring the brightness of supernovae,"},{"time":719375,"text":"and how the brightness of the supernovae"},{"time":721209,"text":"got fainter with distance."},{"time":723380,"text":"And these observations were more complex."},{"time":725833,"text":"They required new technologies and new telescopes,"},{"time":728847,"text":"because the supernovae were in galaxies"},{"time":732897,"text":"that were 2,000 times more distant"},{"time":734855,"text":"than the ones used by Hubble."},{"time":737543,"text":"And it took three years to find just 42 supernovae,"},{"time":742854,"text":"because a supernova only explodes"},{"time":744608,"text":"once every hundred years within a galaxy."},{"time":747690,"text":"Three years to find 42 supernovae"},{"time":749974,"text":"by searching through tens of thousands of galaxies."},{"time":753993,"text":"And once they'd collected their data,"},{"time":755844,"text":"this is what they found."},{"time":759592,"text":"Now, this may not look impressive,"},{"time":762303,"text":"but this is what a revolution in physics looks like:"},{"time":766418,"text":"a line predicting the brightness of a supernova"},{"time":768848,"text":"11 billion light years away,"},{"time":770894,"text":"and a handful of points that don't quite fit that line."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774690,"text":"Small changes give rise to big consequences."},{"time":778803,"text":"Small changes allow us to make discoveries,"},{"time":781751,"text":"like the planet found by Herschel."},{"time":784574,"text":"Small changes turn our understanding"},{"time":786846,"text":"of the universe on its head."},{"time":789247,"text":"So 42 supernovae, slightly too faint,"},{"time":792711,"text":"meaning slightly further away,"},{"time":794720,"text":"requiring that a universe must not just be expanding,"},{"time":797880,"text":"but this expansion must be accelerating,"},{"time":801210,"text":"revealing a component of our universe"},{"time":803156,"text":"which we now call dark energy,"},{"time":805642,"text":"a component that drives this expansion"},{"time":808151,"text":"and makes up 68 percent of the energy budget"},{"time":811178,"text":"of our universe today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":814751,"text":"So what is the next revolution likely to be?"},{"time":818575,"text":"Well, what is dark energy and why does it exist?"},{"time":821294,"text":"Each of these lines shows a different model"},{"time":823622,"text":"for what dark energy might be,"},{"time":826465,"text":"showing the properties of dark energy."},{"time":828946,"text":"They all are consistent with the 42 points,"},{"time":832569,"text":"but the ideas behind these lines"},{"time":834796,"text":"are dramatically different."},{"time":836899,"text":"Some people think about a dark energy"},{"time":839442,"text":"that changes with time,"},{"time":840900,"text":"or whether the properties of the dark energy"},{"time":843188,"text":"are different depending on where you look on the sky."},{"time":845944,"text":"Others make differences and changes"},{"time":847767,"text":"to the physics at the sub-atomic level."},{"time":850815,"text":"Or, they look at large scales"},{"time":853605,"text":"and change how gravity and general relativity work,"},{"time":857170,"text":"or they say our universe is just one of many,"},{"time":859961,"text":"part of this mysterious multiverse,"},{"time":862559,"text":"but all of these ideas, all of these theories,"},{"time":865720,"text":"amazing and admittedly some of them a little crazy,"},{"time":869219,"text":"but all of them consistent with our 42 points."}]},{"cues":[{"time":873246,"text":"So how can we hope to make sense of this"},{"time":875428,"text":"over the next decade?"},{"time":877700,"text":"Well, imagine if I gave you a pair of dice,"},{"time":880930,"text":"and I said you wanted to see whether those dice"},{"time":882929,"text":"were loaded or fair."},{"time":884796,"text":"One roll of the dice would tell you very little,"},{"time":887730,"text":"but the more times you rolled them,"},{"time":889722,"text":"the more data you collected,"},{"time":891644,"text":"the more confident you would become,"},{"time":893816,"text":"not just whether they're loaded or fair,"},{"time":896419,"text":"but by how much, and in what way."},{"time":900317,"text":"It took three years to find just 42 supernovae"},{"time":904119,"text":"because the telescopes that we built"},{"time":907166,"text":"could only survey a small part of the sky."},{"time":910859,"text":"With the LSST, we get a completely new view"},{"time":913524,"text":"of the skies above Chile every three nights."},{"time":917146,"text":"In its first night of operation,"},{"time":919609,"text":"it will find 10 times the number of supernovae"},{"time":922759,"text":"used in the discovery of dark energy."},{"time":925900,"text":"This will increase by 1,000"},{"time":927709,"text":"within the first four months:"},{"time":930202,"text":"1.5 million supernovae by the end of its survey,"},{"time":934986,"text":"each supernova a roll of the dice,"},{"time":938171,"text":"each supernova testing which theories of dark energy"},{"time":941613,"text":"are consistent, and which ones are not."},{"time":945741,"text":"And so, by combining these supernova data"},{"time":949544,"text":"with other measures of cosmology,"},{"time":951820,"text":"we'll progressively rule out the different ideas"},{"time":954710,"text":"and theories of dark energy"},{"time":956686,"text":"until hopefully at the end of this survey around 2030,"},{"time":963828,"text":"we would expect to hopefully see"},{"time":966442,"text":"a theory for our universe,"},{"time":968584,"text":"a fundamental theory for the physics of our universe,"},{"time":971123,"text":"to gradually emerge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":974950,"text":"Now, in many ways, the questions that I posed"},{"time":977342,"text":"are in reality the simplest of questions."},{"time":981703,"text":"We may not know the answers,"},{"time":983457,"text":"but we at least know how to ask the questions."},{"time":987309,"text":"But if looking through tens of thousands of galaxies"},{"time":990427,"text":"revealed 42 supernovae that turned"},{"time":993365,"text":"our understanding of the universe on its head,"},{"time":996844,"text":"when we're working with billions of galaxies,"},{"time":999758,"text":"how many more times are we going to find"},{"time":1001535,"text":"42 points that don't quite match what we expect?"},{"time":1007183,"text":"Like the planet found by Herschel"},{"time":1009940,"text":"or dark energy"},{"time":1012357,"text":"or quantum mechanics or general relativity,"},{"time":1016200,"text":"all ideas that came because the data"},{"time":1018544,"text":"didn't quite match what we expected."},{"time":1021999,"text":"What's so exciting about the next decade of data"},{"time":1025260,"text":"in astronomy is,"},{"time":1026930,"text":"we don't even know how many answers"},{"time":1029141,"text":"are out there waiting,"},{"time":1030941,"text":"answers about our origins and our evolution."},{"time":1034822,"text":"How many answers are out there"},{"time":1035917,"text":"that we don't even know the questions"},{"time":1039211,"text":"that we want to ask?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1041222,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1043169,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}